<bibRefCitation author="Kraus O." box="[1106,1265,975,1002]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 207" refId="ref48861" refString="Kraus O. 1960. Athiopische Diplopoden I. Monographie der Odontopygidae-Odontopyginae (Diplopoda, Spirostreptoidea). Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum van Belgisch-Congo 82: 1 - 207." type="journal article" year="1960">Kraus (1960)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,472,1042,1068]" box="[189,472,1042,1068]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,472,1042,1068]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,472,1042,1068]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Other included species</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,1091,1154]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Fourty-seven, including five species described as new here, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kraus O." box="[919,1066,1091,1117]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 207" refId="ref48861" refString="Kraus O. 1960. Athiopische Diplopoden I. Monographie der Odontopygidae-Odontopyginae (Diplopoda, Spirostreptoidea). Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum van Belgisch-Congo 82: 1 - 207." type="journal article" year="1960">Kraus (1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kraus O." box="[1075,1137,1091,1118]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 143" refId="ref48892" refString="Kraus O. 1966. Phylogenie, Chorologie und Systematik der Odontopygoideen (Diplopoda, Spirostreptomorpha). Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft 512: 1 - 143." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Frederiksen S. B." box="[1156,1394,1091,1117]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="597 - 600" refId="ref48078" refString="Frederiksen S. B. 2013 a. East African odontopygid millipedes 2: A new, geographically disjunct species of Chaleponcus (Attems 1914) from the Pare Mts., Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae). Zootaxa 3636 (4): 597 - 600. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3636.4.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Frederiksen (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vohland K. &amp; Hamer M." box="[189,492,1128,1154]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="251 - 304" refId="ref49696" refString="Vohland K. &amp; Hamer M. 2013. A review of the millipedes (Diplopoda) of Namibia, with identification keys and descriptions of two new genera and five new species. African Invertebrates 54: 251 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.5733 / afin. 054.0112" type="journal article" year="2013">Vohland &amp; Hamer (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Enghoff H." box="[504,678,1128,1154]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref47278" refString="Enghoff H. 2014. A mountain of millipedes I: an endemic species-group of the genus Chaleponcus Attems, 1914, from the Udzungwa Mountains, Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 100: 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2014.100" type="journal article" year="2014">Enghoff (2014</bibRefCitation>
, 2017).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,675,1195,1221]" box="[189,675,1195,1221]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,311,1195,1221]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Enghoff H." box="[504,667,1195,1221]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref47278" refString="Enghoff H. 2014. A mountain of millipedes I: an endemic species-group of the genus Chaleponcus Attems, 1914, from the Udzungwa Mountains, Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 100: 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2014.100" type="journal article" year="2014">Enghoff 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[188,1399,1243,1418]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Differs from other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="1991" box="[523,689,1243,1269]" pageId="37" pageNumber="14" rank="tribe" tribe="Prionopetalini">Prionopetalini</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: proplica and metaplica of gonopod coxa coming together apically and forming a hoodlike cucullus; solenomere long and whiplike, at least twice as long as telomere if stretched out, not spiraled terminally; solenomere without accessory branches or outgrowths (except for sometimes at the very base); telomere proximally folded like a tube or a trough and distally dividing into two or three diverging lamellae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,303,1459,1485]" box="[189,303,1459,1485]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1459,1485]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1459,1485]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,1507,1681]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
About half of the described species occur in southern Africa as far north as 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1235,1507,1533]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[189,344,1544,1570]" name="Mozambique" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Enghoff H." box="[359,528,1544,1570]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref47278" refString="Enghoff H. 2014. A mountain of millipedes I: an endemic species-group of the genus Chaleponcus Attems, 1914, from the Udzungwa Mountains, Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 100: 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2014.100" type="journal article" year="2014">Enghoff 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Further north, the genus is represented in the Eastern Arc by 
<taxonomicName authority="Frederiksen, 2013" authorityName="Frederiksen" authorityYear="2013" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parensis">
<emphasis box="[1266,1398,1545,1571]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">C. parensis</emphasis>
Frederiksen, 2013
</taxonomicName>
, five new species described here and, notably, by the the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kraus" authorityYear="1958" box="[1090,1399,1581,1607]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dabagaensis">
<emphasis box="[1090,1399,1581,1607]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Chaleponcus dabagaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group with 21 species in the Udzungwa Mts and 
<taxonomicName authority="Enghoff, 2017" authorityName="Enghoff" authorityYear="2017" box="[786,1174,1618,1645]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altirungwensis">
<emphasis box="[786,995,1618,1645]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">C. altirungwensis</emphasis>
Enghoff, 2017
</taxonomicName>
from Mt. Rungwe (
<bibRefCitation author="Enghoff H." box="[199,366,1655,1681]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref47278" refString="Enghoff H. 2014. A mountain of millipedes I: an endemic species-group of the genus Chaleponcus Attems, 1914, from the Udzungwa Mountains, Tanzania (Diplopoda, Spirostreptida, Odontopygidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 100: 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2014.100" type="journal article" year="2014">Enghoff 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 2017).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[188,1399,1722,1823]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName authority="Enghoff, 2022" authorityName="Enghoff" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,475,1722,1748]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schioetzae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,475,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Chaleponcus schioetzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[486,580,1723,1749]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Enghoff, 2022" authorityName="Enghoff" authorityYear="2022" box="[644,826,1723,1749]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soerensenae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[644,826,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">C. soerensenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[837,934,1723,1749]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, both from the Uluguru Mts, are very similar, sharing among other things a large metaplical palette; they could be placed in a separate species group, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enghoff" authorityYear="2022" box="[315,471,1796,1823]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schioetzae">
C. 
<emphasis box="[349,471,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">schioetzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, see remarks under 
<taxonomicName authority="Enghoff, 2022" authorityName="Enghoff" authorityYear="2022" box="[783,939,1796,1823]" class="Diplopoda" family="Odontopygidae" genus="Chaleponcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schioetzae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[783,939,1796,1823]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">C. schioetzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[947,1037,1797,1823]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
